Gary Lineker accused Liverpool manager Brendan Rodgers of throwing in the towel by selecting a weakened team against Real Madrid.

Rodgers flew in the face of convention by taking out big names like Steven Gerrard, Raheem Sterling and Mario Balotelli for Liverpool’s biggest European assignment since 2009.

Though they defended stoically, the Premier League team were beaten 1-0 in the Bernabeu by Karim Benzema’s first-half goal and rarely troubled Real goalkeeper Iker Casillas.

