Another ITV pundit, Lee Dixon, added: ‘That team for me says he is prioritising the weekend game against Chelsea. He is saying if we win our last two Champions League games we will probably qualify but it is risky.’

Rodgers accepted Liverpool have their work cut out to get out of Group B. They need to win their final two games, at Ludogorets and home to Basle.

